==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Concentrator
<hw>Con"cen*tra`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mining)</fld>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An apparatus for the separation of dry comminuted ore,
by exposing it to intermittent puffs of air.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Firearms)</fld> <def>A frame or ring of wire or
hard paper fitting into the cartridge case used in some shotguns, and
holding the shot together when discharged, to secure close shooting;
also, a device for slightly narrowing the bore at the muzzle for the
same purpose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concentrical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Concentric</ent>⟦br⟧
